==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Arboreal
<hw>Ar*bo"re*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to a tree, or to trees; of nature of trees.</def>
<rj><au>Cowley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Attached to, found in or upon, or frequenting, woods
or trees; <as>as, <ex>arboreal</ex> animals</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Woodpeckers are eminently <qex>arboreal</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Darwin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arbored</ent>⟦br⟧
